{"id":124,"idInBook":2521,"chapterId":10,"bookId":14,"arabic":"وَعَنْهَا قَالَتْ: فَتَلْتُ قَلَائِدَهَا مِنْ عِهْنٍ كَانَ عِنْدِي ثُمَّ بَعَثَ بِهَا مَعَ أَبِي","english":{"narrator":"She said :","text":"I twisted their garlands from carded wool which I had, then he sent them with my father. \n\nBukhari and Muslim."},"hadithNumber":2521,"hadithId":124,"reference":"10:124","meta":{"id":"mishkat_almasabih","length":4428,"totalChapters":25,"arabic":{"title":"مشكاة المصابيح","author":"الإمام الكاتب التبريزي"},"english":{"title":"Mishkat Al Masabih","author":"Al-Khatib Al-Tabrizi"}},"chapter":{"id":10,"bookId":14,"arabic":"كتاب المناسك","english":"The Rites of Pilgrimage","startHadith":2398,"endHadith":2643,"totalHadiths":246},"version":{"name":"mishkat_almasabih","title":"Mishkat Al Masabih","chapters":25}}